<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="639" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d639">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 847/144.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister for Foreign Affairs
                                    of Panama</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign
                                        Office</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-10-06"><hi rend="italic">October 6, 1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>President Obaldia requests me to convey to you the expressions of his
                            appreciation of your kind congratulations, and I beg that you will
                            accept my own for your benevolent phrases concerning myself. I feel
                            confident that our always pleasant and cordial relations will be
                            continued and aid much toward a satisfactory solution of the affairs
                            between our respective Governments.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Arango.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>